div.div:
We could offer a time-triggered "online"/"offline" schedule that can be set up be the helper.
Example: A local community offering phone services themselves but only at certain times (e.g. 8am - 4pm).
We offer the same thing but 24/7 and also include a fallback in case the helper is either already in a call or the helper does not want to be called directly right now.

switch.text: We could offer a time-triggered "online"/"offline" schedule...

div.div:
By default helpers will not be assigned any calls
As soon as they put themselves "online" (see above) OR accept Calls manually they will get assigned calls either as a local helper or as a mediator (in case of a local concern and no local helper is available at the hotline).
In Both cases (redirect/accept) helpers can filter the calls the will be assigned to (see the following):
